choices.text:
Sally has 3 brothers. Her brothers have 2 sisters. How many sisters does Sally have? Explain your answer
Sally's three siblings are her brother(s). Each of them is married to a sister, which means that each set consists of two people. Therefore, the total number of individuals in these sets (including both members) would be 2 x 3 = 6 - Sally herself being one individual and not part of any group or family unit as such; thus she does have no sisters by marriage either!
